post_text:
Student Handbook - Dress Code
Please note dress & grooming requirements. If your student does not meet these criteria, please correct ASAP. Discipline will be taken for violations starting next week, Aug. 24.

Note:
-Hair color must be neutral tones
-No rattails, Mohawks, symbols/words carved into hair. Bangs must not cover eyes
-No ponytails/buns for male students
-No halter, crop tops, or spaghetti straps
-No rips, tears,or fraying in jeans, shorts, or pants
-Leggings/jeggings not allowed unless they are worn under clothing of appropriate length. Biker/compression shorts may not be worn under short shorts/skirts
-No facial piercings/gauges allowed. Appropriate pierced earrings allowed for girls. No pierced ears allowed for boys

How To Talk to Your Kids About Coronavirus:

While this is an overwhelming time for us all, here are some tips to help you help your kids...
1. Talk to your students about what is going on (see video link below)
2. Limit exposure to news/media
3. Set a routine & goals for the day
4. Help your student process their feelings/questions

I will be posting counseling resources on my webpage regarding how to help your student with worry or anxious feelings. Feel free to contact me at mshafer@stanton.esc18.net with any questions or concerns.

Dear Friends,



The November/December newsletter is available, The Parent and Family Engagement Connection.



It is now available in five languages: English, Spanish, German, Korean, and Vietnamese.

You may print the newsletter, post on your website or link it to your website and social media sites. You can add your own material to it. Due to copyright restrictions you cannot select and reproduce individual articles.

The newsletter is available at https://www.esc16.net/page/title1swi.3_newsletter%20-%20Copy

Articles in this newsletter include: Parent-teacher conference tips, Homework help, Human trafficking protection, Volunteering, and Teen discipline.

post_text:
Parent / Guardian,

At approximately 10:45 am, Stanton High School received a report of a possible firearm on campus. Stanton High school was placed on a precautionary lockdown to provide law enforcement the opportunity to investigate the report. As an additional precaution, Stanton Elementary and Middle School were sheltered in place. Once law enforcement determined there was not a threat to the school, the lockdown was lifted. Students have returned to their normal schedule. Stanton I.S.D. takes all threats seriously and will take the necessary precautions to ensure the protection of our students and staff.

Please let me know if you have any questions or concerns.

post_text:
To answer questions regarding the Elementary School's Dress Code, we're attaching the policy from Elementary Student Handbook (available on the Elementary's website).

Here are the highlights:
-Rips, tears and fraying is allowed in jeans, as long as skin/undergarments is not visible above mid-thigh
-Shorts/skirts should fall mid-thigh in length
-Only neutral hair colors allow (no blotches or stripes)
-No rattails, mohawks, logos, words shaved into hair
-Ponytails and buns are not allowed for male students
-No low-cut styles, halter tops, spaghetti straps (must be 2 in. wide)
-No bare midriffs/crop tops
-Cap, hats, or hoodies cannot be worn inside
-Backpacks must be small enough to fit inside lockers
-No clothing with wrestling pictures, vulgar, alcohol, tobacco, drug, death/violence or objectionable wording/pictures are allowed
